- 'Seasoned gardeners' refers to users who have logged in more than 5 times;
- 'Holding the key to the garden' means users with the 'Admin' role;
- 'Tending to the sales section' means users who are part of the 'Sales' department;
- 'Watered the plants' refers to the total number of activities performed by the users.

- 'garden of departments' refers to the organizational structure where users belong to different departments;
- 'tried to open the garden gate' refers to the login attempts made by the users;
- 'fellow gardeners' refers to the other users in the same department;
- 'unique ID' refers to the user_id, which is a unique identifier for each user.

- 'New User' is defined as a user who logged in within 30 days of joining;
- 'Active User' is defined as a user who logged in between 30 and 90 days after joining;
- 'Inactive User' is defined as a user who logged in more than 90 days after joining;
- A user with no failed login attempts will have a `total_failed_attempts` value of 0.

- 'primary department' refers to the department with `department_id = 1`;
- 'specific role' refers to the role with `role_id = 1`;
- 'active user' refers to a user whose account is active (`is_active = 1`).

- "Recent joiners" refers to users who have joined their respective departments most recently;
- "More than two applications" means the user has accessed more than two different applications recently;
- "More than one role" means the user has been assigned more than one different role.

- "Users with multiple departments" refers to users who are associated with more than one department, with at least one primary department;
- "Users with multiple roles" refers to users who have more than one role assigned;
- "Users with recent activity" refers to users who have had activity logged within the last 30 days;
- "Users with password reset requests" refers to users who have made at least one password reset request;
- "Roles with permissions" refers to roles that have at least one application access permission.

- "most active users" refers to users with the highest total activity;
- "stumbled more times than they've succeeded" refers to users having more failed logins than successful logins;
- "digital garden" is a metaphor for the system or platform being used.

- "active users" refers to users where `is_active = 1`;
- "primary blooms" refers to departments where `is_primary = 1`;
- "moments of sunshine" refers to the count of activity logs;
- "basked in the light" refers to the last activity time.

- Active users are those with `is_active = 1`;
- Regular users are those with `is_superuser = 0`;
- The total number of login attempts is derived from the `login_attempts` table.

- "flower" refers to a user in the context of the database;
- "garden of departments" refers to the departments in the organization;
- "tools" refers to the applications that users can access.

- 'Failed to unlock the gate' refers to failed login attempts;
- 'The highest point of resistance' refers to the user with the highest number of failed login attempts;
- 'Above the average number of failed attempts' means the number of failed login attempts is greater than the average number of failed login attempts.

- "blooming flowers" refers to active users (is_active = 1);
- "primary nurturing grounds" refers to the primary department (is_primary = 1);
- "HR gardeners" refers to the HR department (department_name != 'HR').
